(1) A non-governmental organisation shall be deemed to be established in Zambia although it is organised and has its headquarters or chief place of business outside Zambia, if any of its officer-bearers or members reside in Zambia or are present therein, or if any person in Zambia manages or assists in the management of such organisation or solicits or collects money or subscriptions on its behalf.
